# DTO mapping (handlers)

Full convention: repo root `CLAUDE.md` → **DTO mapping**.

## Do

- Put entity/DTO projection in `Modules.<Module>/Application/Mapping/<Module>Mapping.cs` (`internal static`).
- Handlers: load data → authorize → call mapper → return `Result<T>`.
- EF list/detail queries: expose `Expression<Func<Entity, Dto>>` on the mapper when projecting in SQL.
- Materialize join results then map when EF projection would be unreadable.

## Don't

- Inline `new FooDto(...)` with nested children in handlers (especially when duplicated).
- Add AutoMapper, Mapster, or similar.

## Examples in this repo

| Module | Mapper |
|---|---|
| WorkoutSession | `Application/Mapping/SessionMapping.cs` |
| WorkoutPlan | `Application/Mapping/WorkoutPlanMapping.cs` |
| Exercise | `Application/Mapping/ExerciseMapping.cs` |
| User | `Application/Mapping/UserMapping.cs` |

## Handler shape

```csharp
var nameById = await SessionMapping.GetExerciseNamesAsync(exerciseRepository, session.Exercises, ct);
return Result.Success(SessionMapping.ToActiveSessionDto(session, snapshot, nameById));
```
